HEADWORD: Forfeitable
<hw>For"feit*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Liable to be
forfeited; subject to forfeiture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For the future, uses shall be subject to the statutes of mortmain,
and <qex>forfeitable</qex>, like the lands themselves.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Forfeiter</ent>⟦br⟧
